title: For Sale:  US Model 1873 Bayonet for the Trapdoor Springfield
postcontent: The Model 1873 bayonet was made for the 1873 Springfield Trapdoor Rifle, and is similar to earlier Civil War bayonets. Indeed, the Army had many of the earlier bayonets cold pressed to reduce the socket diameter to fit the ’73 Springfield. It’s the first US bayonet to be blued, and I think it’s the last of the US Army standard issue socket bayonets. It is marked with a “US” at the base of the blade. This bayonet is free from rust.The scabbard shown is the 1887 version for the 1873 bayonet, with a brass hook permanently attached leather frog instead of a belt loop. This was intended to be inserted through one of the loops in the Mills woven cartridge belt. Scabbards are hard to find in good condition, and this one is in good condition. Leather intact and still relatively supple. Asking $100.00 cash. This is a great price for this, so please, do not email with other offers. Thanks for looking!
